Police say three armed suspects approached a stationary vehicle on Friday afternoon and then opened fire on the driver JOHANNESBURG - A man has been shot and wounded in an attempted robbery on the Grayston bridge in Sandton. Police say three armed suspects approached a stationary vehicle on Friday afternoon and then opened fire on the driver. The police's Granville Meyer says no arrests have yet been made. “The suspects got out of the vehicle and approached the man in his vehicle, they wanted to rob him. The suspects then started to shot at the victim, who is currently in hospital. His condition is currently unknown.”